title: No, the Galaxy S9 Plus hasn't been spotted on Geekbench – here's why
description: ![Galaxy S8deal]()### Alexa’s new whisper mode rolls out in US today – here’s how to enable it](https://www.trustedreviews.com/news/how-to-enable-alexa-whisper-mode-echo-3607478 "Alexa’s new whisper mode rolls out in US today – here’s how toenable it")  * But if that isn’t enough to convince you, maybe this will.We uncovered an identical Geekbench[listing](https://browser.geekbench.com/v4/cpu/3431561), which dates back toJuly. _Sure_ , there’s a chance a prototype could have been functional backthen, but it would have been impossible for it to have been running Android8.0 Oreo, as the filing states.A handset had to have been tampered with to generate the result – and it isn’toverly difficult to do. There are a number of applications available forrooted Android smartphones that let you alter system information.The moral of the story? Don’t believe everything you read online.**Are you looking forward to the Galaxy S9 and Galaxy S9 Plus? Do you thinkthey will ship with at least 6GB of RAM? Be sure to let us know over onFacebook or Twitter @TrustedReviews.**
